        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 4:12PM EDT by NWS Wilmington OH</headline>
        <description>At 411 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was located over Springboro,
moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 45 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Hail may cause minor damage to
vegetation.

Locations impacted include...
Middletown, Miamisburg, Lebanon, Springboro, Franklin, Bellbrook,
Blanchester, Waynesville, Morrow, Hunter, Clarksville, Harveysburg,
Spring Valley, Corwin, Centerville, Paintersville, Fort Ancient,
Lytle, Lumberton, and Mount Holly.

This includes the following Interstates...
I-71 in Ohio between mile markers 31 and 51.
I-75 in Ohio near mile marker 32, and between mile markers 36 and
44.

If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a sturdy building.

To report hazardous weather conditions, go to our website at
weather.gov/iln and submit your report via social media, when you can
do so safely.
</description>
